description.en: The Machine Learning Test Ontology was built to characterize failures that have been identified during the use of machine learning tools, in particular the TensorFlow tool.

comments.en: An ontology to describe the testing process in Machine Learning tools to describe how failures occur in these systems. Created by Alexandre Locci Martins and Ana Cristina Vierira de Melo.

comment.undefined: TensorFlow uses compute graphs to define and manage its tasks. The graph implements the definition, construction, partition, optimization, operation, and execution of calculations.

The runtime implements the management of sessions, thread pools, and executors. TensorFlow has a common runtime (core/common runtime) and a distribution runtime (core/distributed runtime). Common runtime supports theexecutions on a local machine, and distribution runtime allows to deploy TensorFlow on distributed ones.

comment.undefined: "TensorFlow is an open-source platform developed by Google for the purpose of machine learning and deep learning. It is widely used to develop and train machine learning models."

The goal of TensorFlow Model Analysis is to provide a mechanism for model evaluation in TFX. TensorFlow Model Analysis allows to perform model evaluations in the TFX pipeline, and view resultant metrics and plots in a Jupyter notebook.
Jupyter Notebook environment that is not necessary be setting and runs in the cloud.

comment.en: API's . The API's function is to link between different applications serving the user. They enable integration between different systems and make user actions faster with the expected responses. The API always works in the background, so the average user does not even see the API in operation. TensorFlow provides APIs in many programming languages as C, C++, Java, and Python, which one are located in the python, c, cc and java directories.

Refers to a system that is being tested for correct operation. According to ISTQB it is the test object. From a unit testing perspective, the system under test represents all of the classes in a test that are not predefined pieces of code like stubs or even mocks.
